THE SA National Defence Force yesterday confirmed that one of its soldiers shot dead his girlfriend and her female friend, wounding two others in the process, including a police officer who tried to intervene, in Ntuzuma, outside Durban. A member of SANDF from 8 South African Infantry Battalion (8 SAI) in Upington, Northern Cape, in possession of an R4 assault rifle, fatally shot two civilian females and wounded a third civilian (female) and a policeman in the Ntuzuma area in the KwaZulu-Natal province, a statement from defence headquarters said.It said the police had activated their Tactical Response Team (TRT) to track down the soldier. The military police had also been dispatched to the scene of the shootings. The SANDF will co-operate with the law enforcement agencies to ensure that the law takes its course. The SANDF will not tolerate, condone nor dismiss any type or form of ill-discipline committed by any of its members regardless of rank, status or position held no matter the circumstances under which the transgressions are committed. ANA